summary: i love that the mighty nein will, like, kill a whole crew of pirates for literally no reason other than they got caught up doing...
body: i love that the mighty nein will, like, kill a whole crew of pirates for literally no reason other than they got caught up doing it and don’t know how to get out of the encounter. but when confronted with an undead sealady who’s been systematically murdering whole ships full of people for god knows how long, and even attempted to murder fjord not too long ago, they’re like “meh. let her go. not worth it.”
